VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \.filter\s*\(\s*["']|\.filter\s*\(\s*f["']|\.filter\s*\(\s*["'][^"']*["']\s*%
WHEN EXPR MISSING:bindparams|bindparam|:(?!:)\w|params
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects SQLAlchemy filter() calls using raw string conditions instead of ORM column expressions.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for filter() with Raw String Condition.
